This memorandum, addressed to the Secretary of State, delegates certain authorities under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to provide assistance to Ukraine. The delegated authorities include the power to determine whether it is in the security interests of the United States to provide up to $100 million in assistance without any legal restrictions, as well as the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $100 million in defense articles and services from the Department of Defense for the purpose of assisting Ukraine. The memorandum also instructs the publication of this document in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr.